Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.60,0:01:39.00,Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, I’ve eaten far too much lunch.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.00,0:01:41.90,Top,,0,0,0,,I’ll never be able to keep awake next lesson.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.90,0:01:43.44,Top,,0,0,0,,It’s all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.44,0:01:45.77,Top,,0,0,0,,We’ve got art with Miss Walker this afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.77,0:01:47.71,Top,,0,0,0,,Whatever you do, it doesn’t matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.01,0:01:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don’t say that, \Nthat's not fair to Miss Walker.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.34,0:01:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s a kind and nice teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.35,0:01:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.11,0:01:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you two always enjoy it.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.38,0:01:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re good at drawing \Nand get praised every time.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.85,0:01:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.32,0:02:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t enjoy it one bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.96,0:02:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be silly, Doris.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.36,0:02:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, it’s time!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.24,0:02:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.19,0:02:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.76,0:02:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I’ll use it for a bit of a rest. {/to take it easy}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.43,0:02:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll catch a nap.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.48,0:02:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we’ll be making trinket boxes \Nfrom these boards.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.88,0:02:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You may design them however you like—\Ncarve on the lid, paint on the surface—anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.25,0:02:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want is something original and pretty.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.39,0:02:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve written the steps out \Non a handout for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.69,0:02:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week, at the end of this lesson, \Nwe’ll have a review.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.83,0:02:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you must finish them by then.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.09,0:02:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker, we can’t possibly \Ndo it in so short a time.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.86,0:02:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve a whole week, haven't you? The art room \Nshall stay open after school until bedtime.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.10,0:02:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You may use the tools freely. \NNow, let us begin.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.08,0:03:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to use my time wisely... \NWhat kind of trinket box should I make?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.25,0:03:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigh... Perhaps, I’ll paint a picture on the lid?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.75,0:03:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... So much for a nap today.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.02,0:03:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind—Miss Walker always says the same thing afterwards, remember?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.98,0:03:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Set yourselves free, \Nand savour the joy of imagination!”
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.60,0:03:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.50,0:03:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See now?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.57,0:03:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once she starts sketching, \Nit’s always the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.38,0:03:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so carefree! {think she means it as "scatterbrained"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.74,0:03:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if we were on another planet entirely!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.88,0:03:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. \NLet's make a productive use of it, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.86,0:03:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Doris and Vera aren't in the least bothered \Nabout running out of time!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.46,0:03:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve no time to waste worrying about others.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.06,0:03:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We must hurry too.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.26,0:03:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.55,0:04:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.54,0:04:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It swerved! {lit: curved/bended - dunno what english verb to use with this kind of action}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.04,0:04:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You gave me such a fright! \NI thought you’d cut your hand or something.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.43,0:04:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not easy for me. {lit: it's not going well - think she means this as response to janet: "this is important to me"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.06,0:04:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan, you’ll ruin the saw like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.40,0:04:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,First, hold the board steady. \NGrip it like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.55,0:04:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Only put in your strength when you push, \Nand find your rhythm.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.57,0:04:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.91,0:04:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t rush, go for "slow and steady."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.85,0:04:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is creating something yourself, \Neven if it’s clumsy at first.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.19,0:04:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! I’ve done it!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:49.39,0:04:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.57,0:04:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! You're a natural, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.96,0:04:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a rather handy girl, you know. {skillful; skilful; adroit; dexterous; dextrous; deft; nimble; handy}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.20,0:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s nothing much, so why even bother? {lit: Even if you could do that, it wouldn't make any difference - think she means "what's the point, if it's nothing special and it'll never help you in life"}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.07,0:05:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense! Better to be able to do it than not.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.09,0:05:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, by all means!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.64,0:05:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the furniture shop will come begging you \Nto become a master craftsman before long.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.11,0:05:11.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,Furniture shop, right...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.60,0:05:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bother... All the teachers set us up \Nwith extra work this week.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.42,0:05:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Miss Roberts \Nwith her problem practice handouts,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.06,0:05:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle with her essay...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.61,0:05:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis and her timeline tables, {lit: history chronological table}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.26,0:05:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and on top of it all—\Nthat wretched trinket box!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.13,0:05:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The mistresses only ever think \Nof their own lessons.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.20,0:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially Miss Walker, \Njust living in a world of her own. {my pace = (doing things) one's own way (esp. in an inconsiderate manner)}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.17,0:05:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about eccentric artists.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.54,0:05:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Doris, weren’t you given extra work by Mam’zelle?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.32,0:05:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you manage?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.55,0:05:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did a bit during art just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.45,0:05:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Figures. But what about the art class? \NYou’ve not done a thing yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.64,0:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it’s quite all right! \NI’ve got it all thought out.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.65,0:06:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be too late if you don’t hurry. Quick! {?? could be "vera kara" = because of you?}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.27,0:06:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait for me, Doris!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.84,0:06:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we going?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.04,0:06:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind, just come along.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.53,0:06:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure it was around here somewhere…
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.09,0:06:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there it is!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.57,0:06:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.55,0:06:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a craftsman here?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.54,0:06:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet, I’m still an apprentice.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.07,0:06:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Making things must be a wonderful job.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.77,0:06:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m Doris—what’s your name?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.06,0:06:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.48,0:06:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Steve.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.02,0:06:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Well then, Steve, could you make something like a little trinket box, about this size?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.35,0:07:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make anything!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.04,0:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you make one for me? \NI haven’t much money, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.59,0:07:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Doris! What are you... {anata}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.03,0:07:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a plain box will do.\NNothing fancy, just a box.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.73,0:07:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d have to ask the master.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.73,0:07:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not allowed to take on work by myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.24,0:07:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s all right, Steve.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.44,0:07:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest assured, charming young ladies—\Nhe's only half-trained, but keen as mustard!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.04,0:07:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him do it for practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.54,0:07:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Master?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.40,0:07:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, but only so long as you make one \Nthat won’t bring embarrassment to our shop.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:30.78,0:07:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I won’t!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.42,0:07:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief! \NThank you, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.35,0:07:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Vera, what about you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.62,0:07:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Er... I mean... we shouldn't...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.42,0:07:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll just get the box made \Nand then paint something on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.36,0:07:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think I will, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.80,0:07:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I’ll work my hardest on it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.92,0:07:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You asked a furniture maker’s apprentice?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.64,0:07:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.43,0:07:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s only the box!\NOnly because I’m hopeless with a saw myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.25,0:08:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll do the finishing touches myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.45,0:08:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve heaps of other homework, \Nthere’s simply not enough time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.75,0:08:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He said if we brought our own wood, \Nhe’d only charge for his time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.19,0:08:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Only five shillings!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.44,0:08:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.86,0:08:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well—that’s rather cheap.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.44,0:08:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it? And you should see \Nthat apprentice boy, ever so shy and sweet.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.33,0:08:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we barely smiled at him, \Nhe blushed scarlet!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.45,0:08:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, it’s not right to tease \Nor take advantage of such a simple soul.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.74,0:08:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not taking advantage—\Nhe said himself he wanted to do it for practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.98,0:08:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, now I can tackle \Nthe rest of my homework in peace.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.35,0:08:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What will Miss Walker say if she finds out?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.94,0:08:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right! She's so kind, more like a friend than a teacher. She won't even punish us.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.99,0:08:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite so. She’ll just frown a little
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.00,0:08:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, “Why, Doris, you seem suddenly clever with your hands!”
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.81,0:09:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s the end for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.62,0:09:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's half past eight, we must go.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.48,0:09:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.39,0:09:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, what about you?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.75,0:09:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm almost finished. \NGo on ahead without me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.77,0:09:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Goodnight, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.36,0:09:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take long.{\we're going ahead}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.26,0:09:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.93,0:09:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Not too shabby…
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.97,0:09:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, crumbs! The lid doesn’t fit!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.87,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I could trim it down...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.17,0:09:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that won't do.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.67,0:09:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've carved it right to the edge—\Nif I cut it, it’ll ruin the art.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.49,0:09:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How didn’t I notice before?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.64,0:09:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And after all the work I’ve put in…
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.46,0:09:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.89,0:09:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are, the planks,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.91,0:09:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for Vera’s and mine. \NBe a sweetheart, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.42,0:09:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.20,0:10:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is my friend, Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.10,0:10:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s something to ask you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.87,0:10:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Steve.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.24,0:10:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... The measurements are all a bit off.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.28,0:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It won’t make a proper box like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.72,0:10:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But this picture is ace!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.48,0:10:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.79,0:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, quite remarkably done.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.70,0:10:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! I carved it myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.42,0:10:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is meant to be the lid, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.65,0:10:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I’ll make the box to fit it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.60,0:10:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oh, no...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.30,0:10:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not what I meant, I just hoped \Nyou'd help me get the measurements right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.97,0:10:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on, let him do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.30,0:10:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But Doris...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.27,0:10:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You carved the lid yourself, all right. \NNo harm in letting him make the box.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.54,0:10:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.11,0:10:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.48,0:10:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.94,0:11:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, Pat! You mean you’ve had that apprentice Steve make it for you?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.44,0:11:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... I didn’t really mean to. \NIt just sort of happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.00,0:11:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember what Miss Walker said—\Nwhat matters is creating it yourself, however clumsy.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.84,0:11:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.21,0:11:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I did carve the lid myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.46,0:11:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat…
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.96,0:11:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I’m off to do my history charts.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.25,0:11:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for both of us, mind you. {lit: You'll also be able to copy it after}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.12,0:11:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.35,0:11:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t say I didn’t warn you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.03,0:11:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There! French prep finished!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.47,0:11:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam’zelle won’t be able \Nto call it abominable now!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.44,0:11:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the others are still in the art room?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.44,0:11:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect so.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.11,0:11:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn’t it lucky we asked Steve?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.28,0:11:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We're already drowning in other homework, we did the right thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.08,0:11:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.33,0:12:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Bother! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.23,0:12:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.46,0:12:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve chiselled away too much!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.70,0:12:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right—just do the same on all the other notches,\N and it'd look neat when finished. {?????? lit: chisel them all there, remove the water, and it'd feel fresh - dunno what's that water, i assume it "misu" somehow = "remove the mistake" = "make all those little dots the same" (dunno what to call them)}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.32,0:12:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.81,0:12:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... It might even be better that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.41,0:12:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it steady.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.11,0:12:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tie the string now to keep it in place.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.08,0:12:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.09,0:12:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is coming out so neat, you're lucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.26,0:12:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard at first, \Nbut once I got the hang of it, it was fun.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.16,0:12:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to use mine for jewellery.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.84,0:12:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll keep sweets in mine!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.35,0:12:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just like you, Joan!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.81,0:12:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.71,0:13:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Er... Which way to the dormitory?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.86,0:13:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a girls’ school, young man!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.65,0:13:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen are not allowed in the dormitories.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.02,0:13:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... That's a nuisance.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.86,0:13:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for a certain Doris...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.62,0:13:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Steve!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.13,0:13:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.40,0:13:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to deliver this, \Nbut didn’t know where to go.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.15,0:13:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia O'Sullivan!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.27,0:13:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Mam’zelle!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.70,0:13:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.45,0:13:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, we just asked the carpenter in town \Nto do a bit of repairs for us... {lit: shop in town}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.61,0:13:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.88,0:13:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Here you are.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.55,0:13:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pay me next time you’re in town.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.46,0:13:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.97,0:13:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.15,0:13:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.08,0:13:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, fetch it yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.55,0:13:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To have it delivered—by a boy, too!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.72,0:13:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, abominable!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.79,0:13:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I—I’m sorry, Mam’zelle. \NI’ll be more careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.15,0:13:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminy! My heart very nearly stopped!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.65,0:13:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Dash! He's finished them all already!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.01,0:14:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Steve's even decorated \Nand varnished them for us. {probably means that they wanted to carve something on the lid themselves to make each look unique}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.84,0:14:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He meant well.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.71,0:14:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We never told him it was for our art class.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.41,0:14:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.67,0:14:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? It’s beautifully made.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.29,0:14:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m handing it in as it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.19,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they’re all a little different, so it's all right. {to hand them in as our own}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.67,0:14:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.79,0:14:21.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,It may be a little too fancy, though... {??? not sure what she means - a little too sweet/good - probably that it looks too good for something she could've possibly done herself}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.92,0:14:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There! Just a coat of polish and mine’s done. {/varnish}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.27,0:14:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Good! I think I’ll manage to finish mine \Nin time too. Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.31,0:14:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like celebrating!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.95,0:14:43.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can’t help feeling uneasy \Nunless I’ve added something myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.65,0:14:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Time’s up! Let’s go.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.94,0:14:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.52,0:14:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.36,0:14:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's very well done, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.50,0:15:00.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Well, this will have to do. \NI’ll hand this in.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.77,0:15:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, let’s unveil your works. {???? dunno what's that ***kai but gotta be some "conference/assembly" so probably "presentation of your works"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.24,0:15:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please place your boxes on the centre table.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.96,0:15:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When they're all on display like this, \Nours look the smartest, don’t you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.44,0:15:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the time limit, \Nyou’ve all done well.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.74,0:15:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Each piece is different, \Nand very interesting.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.58,0:15:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what do we think of this one?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.51,0:15:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d say it’s most carefully done.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.68,0:15:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the carving is lovely.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.85,0:15:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—the shape is plain, but the rounded corners \Ngive it a soft, modern feel.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.09,0:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who made this one?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.47,0:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.93,0:16:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought. \NIt feels very Isabel-like, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.86,0:16:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were picky, I’d say it’s a little too perfect. {dunno what she means; totonou = to be well-ordered; to be well-proportioned; to be harmonious}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.43,0:16:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it could have used a bit more colour.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.67,0:16:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm! This one has real presence in it. {impressiveness; impact; force; intensity; presence; appeal; strength; punch; edge; vigor}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.37,0:16:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.77,0:16:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tried to assemble it, \Nthe measurements didn’t quite match,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.46,0:16:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But somehow, it feels warm and inviting.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.58,0:16:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It really shows Joan’s character.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.65,0:16:29.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,I also should have done \Neverything myself, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.79,0:16:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This dahlia carving is beautiful!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.36,0:16:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker, that’s actually a rose.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.98,0:16:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.17,0:16:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that concludes today’s session.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.92,0:16:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Miss Walker, but there's still... {three fancy boxes left}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.14,0:16:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Those whose work has been reviewed may leave. The rest of you, stay. {meaning she only reviewed the plain ones, not the fancy ones}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.00,0:17:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick up your pieces now.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.66,0:17:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All three are really well done.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.73,0:17:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's this feeling?\NI can’t hear your voices in them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.80,0:17:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closely.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.20,0:17:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All the other pieces seem to be chattering away. {/talking}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.77,0:17:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all asserting themselves, \Nshowing who made them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.77,0:17:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they’re a little uneven, \Naren’t they charming?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.34,0:17:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is certainly very precise and skilfully done. \NYet it doesn’t say anything about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.38,0:17:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker, I had someone else make my box.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.27,0:17:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I carved the lid myself, but the measurements were wrong, and it became a hassle.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.08,0:17:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.78,0:17:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker, I didn't make mine either. {/me too}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.97,0:17:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn’t enough time. \NThere was so much homework this week...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.17,0:17:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mam'zelle said I’d be thunderstruck \Nif I scored poorly on the next French test. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.27,0:17:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I’m not good at art.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.24,0:17:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m clumsy...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.34,0:18:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m hopeless at both drawing and craft!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.55,0:18:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only dance, somewhat.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.82,0:18:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured if I could just dance well, \Nthe rest didn’t matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.82,0:18:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just dance well,” you say?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.52,0:18:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.79,0:18:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,With that attitude, \Nyour dancing will never improve.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.81,0:18:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no…
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.81,0:18:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Doris, Pat, Vera—hands out, like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.03,0:18:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that makes human hands different from other animals is that we use them to create things.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.84,0:18:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have similar hands, yet what Van Gogh, \NCézanne, Picasso created are all different.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.55,0:18:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That is called individuality.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.10,0:18:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what we call art—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.35,0:18:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,creating something only you can make.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.89,0:18:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who can’t uphold this basic attitude, \Ncan't get good at dancing,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.29,0:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,let alone live her life in her own way.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.46,0:18:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a shame.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.50,0:18:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These hands could do so much more.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.37,0:18:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to know the joy of creation.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.07,0:18:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's lesson was very disappointing.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.57,0:19:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give marks later.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.85,0:19:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone, it’s tea time.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.87,0:19:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.42,0:19:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t expect Miss Walker to get so angry.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.86,0:19:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it’s all over now... \NWe failed. {lit: we're done for, failing mark}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.73,0:19:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s our own fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.10,0:19:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't doubt Miss Walker \Nknows {\i1}the joy of creation{\i0}, all right! {18:52}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.80,0:19:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she spends class time drawing \Nwhatever she likes while leaving us to our own devices!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.27,0:19:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not true, Doris.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.61,0:19:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.81,0:19:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker is drawing for {\i1}your{\i0} sake.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.91,0:19:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For us?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.02,0:19:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives her drawings as parting gifts \Nto the graduating students.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.66,0:19:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She sketches your work \Nduring first form lessons.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.44,0:19:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? So then, those sketches…
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.06,0:20:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These are portraits of you \NMiss Walker draws with all her heart,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.30,0:20:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so you would never forget how you felt \Nwhen you first started studying at St. Clare's.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.45,0:20:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.26,0:20:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s my drawing.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.42,0:20:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one’s mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.29,0:20:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{???}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.16,0:20:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.23,0:20:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.33,0:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do let us try making it again, Miss Walker.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.78,0:20:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.94,0:20:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel ashamed for the careless attitude \Nthat I was taking your classes with.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.14,0:20:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry! I was so wrong \Nin my judgement of you!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.18,0:20:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.78,0:20:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so frustrating! \NI'm incredibly angry at myself now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That feeling is important.{?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.32,0:20:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pour it into your work, it will surely become something wonderful, such as your dancing.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.86,0:21:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Walker...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.30,0:21:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat and the others sure are late.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.74,0:21:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet they're gonna work all night.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.71,0:21:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminy!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.05,0:21:22.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,Pat, Doris, Vera... do your best!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.12,0:21:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve got special permission from Headmistress, \Nso pace yourselves accordingly. {lit: don't push yourself too much}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.13,0:21:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.96,0:21:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. I'll get to it too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.37,0:21:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Vera the model today?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.70,0:21:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Finally I can draw her as intended.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.04,0:21:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, during my regular classes, Vera...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.64,0:21:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I promise I won’t doze off in class again.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.29,0:22:05.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Isabel, I’ve finally realised \Nthe joy of making something yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.42,0:22:10.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,And how much thought and care \NMiss Walker puts into her lessons.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.90,0:22:17.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,She’s such a remarkable artist, \Nand an extraordinary teacher too.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.32,0:23:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, do you know Gladys?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.29,0:23:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl working out in the dining hall lately, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.55,0:23:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—have you seen her hands?\N They are awfully red and cracked!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.52,0:23:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.46,0:23:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She washes hundreds of plates every day.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.53,0:23:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Her father passed away, they said.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.28,0:23:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So she’s working instead of going to school?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.23,0:23:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I've got an idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.67,0:23:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too, Pat!{??}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.87,0:23:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start a cheering club for Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.54,0:23:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.04,0:24:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Run, Gladys!" {another reference to hashire melos, sasuga}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.29,0:24:03.73,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 22 \NRun, Gladys! {走れ! グラディス}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.31,0:24:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss it!
